{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":613,"text":"I worked on a film called \"Apollo 13,\""},{"time":2641,"text":"and when I worked on this film, I discovered something"},{"time":4521,"text":"about how our brains work, and how our brains work"},{"time":6984,"text":"is that, when we're sort of infused with"},{"time":9263,"text":"either enthusiasm or awe or fondness or whatever,"},{"time":13509,"text":"it changes and alters our perception of things."},{"time":15917,"text":"It changes what we see. It changes what we remember."},{"time":18094,"text":"And as an experiment, because I dauntingly create"},{"time":21602,"text":"a task for myself of recreating a Saturn V launch"},{"time":25522,"text":"for this particular movie, because I put it out there,"},{"time":28944,"text":"I felt a little nervous about it, so I need to do an experiment"},{"time":31001,"text":"and bring a group of people like this in a projection room"},{"time":34609,"text":"and play this stock footage, and when I played this"},{"time":37289,"text":"stock footage, I simply wanted to find out"},{"time":40090,"text":"what people remembered, what was memorable about it?"},{"time":43505,"text":"What should I actually try to replicate?"},{"time":45508,"text":"What should I try to emulate to some degree?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49279,"text":"So this is the footage that I was showing everybody."},{"time":52368,"text":"And what I discovered is, because of the nature"},{"time":55050,"text":"of the footage and the fact that we're doing this film,"},{"time":57248,"text":"there was an emotion that was built into it"},{"time":59201,"text":"and our collective memories of what this launch meant to us"},{"time":62279,"text":"and all these various things."},{"time":63953,"text":"When I showed it, and I asked, immediately after"},{"time":65985,"text":"the screening was over, what they thought of it,"},{"time":68776,"text":"what was your memorable shots, they changed them."},{"time":71242,"text":"They were -- had camera moves on them."},{"time":73620,"text":"They had all kinds of things. Shots were combined,"},{"time":76296,"text":"and I was just really curious, I mean, what the hell"},{"time":79278,"text":"were you looking at just a few minutes ago"},{"time":80645,"text":"and how come, how'd you come up with this sort of description?"},{"time":84489,"text":"And what I discovered is, what I should do is not actually"},{"time":88337,"text":"replicate what they saw, is replicate what they remembered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92027,"text":"So this is our footage of the launch, based on, basically,"},{"time":96009,"text":"taking notes, asking people what they thought, and then"},{"time":98717,"text":"the combination of all the different shots and all"},{"time":101159,"text":"the different things put together created their sort of"},{"time":103087,"text":"collective consciousness of what they remembered"},{"time":105126,"text":"it looked like, but not what it really looked like."},{"time":106776,"text":"So this is what we created for \"Apollo 13.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":109774,"text":"(Launch noises)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114241,"text":"So literally what you're seeing now is the confluence"},{"time":117007,"text":"of a bunch of different people, a bunch of different memories,"},{"time":119068,"text":"including my own, of taking a little bit of liberty"},{"time":122366,"text":"with the subject matter."},{"time":124090,"text":"I basically shot everything with short lenses,"},{"time":126727,"text":"which means that you're very close to the action,"},{"time":128644,"text":"but framed it very similarly to the long lens shots"},{"time":130934,"text":"which gives you a sense of distance, so I was basically"},{"time":133574,"text":"was setting up something that would remind you"},{"time":135558,"text":"of something you haven't really quite seen before. (Music)"},{"time":139030,"text":"And then I'm going to show you exactly what it is"},{"time":141561,"text":"that you were reacting to when you were reacting to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145162,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158072,"text":"Tom Hanks: Hello, Houston, this is Odyssey."},{"time":160187,"text":"It's good to see you again. (Cheers) (Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162978,"text":"Rob Legato: I pretend they're clapping for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165418,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167576,"text":"So now I'm in a parking lot. Basically it's a tin can,"},{"time":170981,"text":"and I'm basically recreating the launch with"},{"time":172806,"text":"fire extinguishers, fire, I have wax that I threw"},{"time":177145,"text":"in front of the lens to look like ice, and so basically"},{"time":180490,"text":"if you believed any of the stuff that I just showed you,"},{"time":183307,"text":"what you were reacting to, what you're emoting to,"},{"time":186488,"text":"is something that's a total falsehood, and I found that"},{"time":188923,"text":"really kind of fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190317,"text":"And in this particular case, this is the climax of the movie,"},{"time":193293,"text":"and, you know, the weight of achieving it was simply"},{"time":196502,"text":"take a model, throw it out of a helicopter, and shoot it."},{"time":200072,"text":"And that's simply what I did."},{"time":202075,"text":"That's me shooting, and I'm a fairly mediocre operator,"},{"time":204552,"text":"so I got that nice sense of verisimilitude, of a kind of,"},{"time":208091,"text":"you know, following the rocket all the way down,"},{"time":210923,"text":"and giving that little sort of edge, I was desperately"},{"time":212602,"text":"trying to keep it in frame. So then I come up to the next thing."},{"time":216102,"text":"We had a NASA consultant who was actually an astronaut,"},{"time":218699,"text":"who was actually on some of the missions, of Apollo 15,"},{"time":221704,"text":"and he was there to basically double check my science."},{"time":225223,"text":"And, I guess somebody thought they needed to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228744,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230476,"text":"I don't know why, but they thought they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233064,"text":"So we were, he's a hero, he's an astronaut, and"},{"time":237206,"text":"we're all sort of excited, and, you know, I gave myself"},{"time":240012,"text":"the liberty of saying, you know, some of the shots I did"},{"time":242483,"text":"didn't really suck that bad."},{"time":244892,"text":"And so maybe, you know, we were feeling kind of a little"},{"time":248152,"text":"good about it, so I brought him in here, and he needed"},{"time":250609,"text":"to really check and see what we were doing,"},{"time":253146,"text":"and basically give us our A plus report card,"},{"time":256132,"text":"and so I showed him some shots we were working on,"},{"time":258097,"text":"and waiting for the reaction that you hope for,"},{"time":261207,"text":"which is what I got. (Music) (Launch noises)"},{"time":264296,"text":"So I showed him these two shots,"},{"time":266335,"text":"and then he basically told me what he thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269752,"text":"(\"That's wrong\") (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272289,"text":"Okay. (Laughter)"},{"time":275248,"text":"It's what you dream about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277172,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280172,"text":"So what I got from him is, he turned to me and said,"},{"time":283679,"text":"\"You would never, ever design a rocket like that."},{"time":287133,"text":"You would never have a rocket go up"},{"time":288382,"text":"while the gantry arms are going out. Can you imagine"},{"time":290443,"text":"the tragedy that could possibly happen with that?"},{"time":292498,"text":"You would never, ever design a rocket like that.\""},{"time":295340,"text":"And he was looking at me. It's like, Yeah, I don't know"},{"time":297487,"text":"if you noticed, but I'm the guy out in the parking lot"},{"time":299497,"text":"recreating one of America's finest moments with"},{"time":301425,"text":"fire extinguishers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303084,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305443,"text":"And I'm not going to argue with you. You're an astronaut,"},{"time":308371,"text":"a hero, and I'm from New Jersey, so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310648,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312347,"text":"I'm just going to show you some footage."},{"time":314384,"text":"I'm just going to show you some footage, and tell me what you think."},{"time":316994,"text":"And then I did kind of get the reaction I was hoping for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319417,"text":"So I showed him this, and this is actual footage"},{"time":321456,"text":"that he was on. This is Apollo 15. This was his mission."},{"time":325001,"text":"So I showed him this, and the reaction I got was interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330277,"text":"(\"That's wrong too.\") (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333061,"text":"So, and what happened was, I mean, what I sort of intuned"},{"time":336295,"text":"in that is that he remembered it differently."},{"time":338777,"text":"He remembered that was a perfectly safe sort of gantry"},{"time":341121,"text":"system, perfectly safe rocket launch, because he's sitting"},{"time":343824,"text":"in a rocket that has, like, a hundred thousand pounds"},{"time":346047,"text":"of thrust, built by the lowest bidder."},{"time":348321,"text":"He was hoping it was going to work out okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350576,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353345,"text":"So he twisted his memory around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355489,"text":"Now, Ron Howard ran into Buzz Aldrin, who was not"},{"time":358563,"text":"on the movie, so he had no idea that we were faking"},{"time":360878,"text":"any of this footage, and he just responded"},{"time":363104,"text":"as he would respond, and I'll run this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365934,"text":"Ron Howard: Buzz Aldrin came up to me"},{"time":368368,"text":"and said, \"Hey, that launch footage, I saw some shots"},{"time":372806,"text":"I'd never seen before. Did you guys, what vault did you find"},{"time":377804,"text":"that stuff in?\" And I said, \"Well, no vault, Buzz,"},{"time":380265,"text":"we generated all that from scratch.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":383683,"text":"And he said, \"Huh, that's pretty good. Can we use it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":387587,"text":"(Explosion) (\"Sure\") (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391043,"text":"RL: I think he's a great American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":396751,"text":"So, \"Titanic\" was, if you don't know the story,"},{"time":400054,"text":"doesn't end well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401794,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404575,"text":"Jim Cameron actually photographed the real Titanic."},{"time":407726,"text":"So he basically set up, or basically shattered"},{"time":410007,"text":"the suspension of disbelief, because what he photographed"},{"time":412410,"text":"was the real thing, a Mir sub going down, or actually"},{"time":415837,"text":"two Mir subs going down to the real wreck,"},{"time":418180,"text":"and he created this very haunting footage."},{"time":420217,"text":"It's really beautiful, and it conjures up all these"},{"time":423090,"text":"various different emotions, but he couldn't photograph"},{"time":425284,"text":"everything, and to tell the story,"},{"time":428013,"text":"I had to fill in the gaps, which is now rather daunting,"},{"time":429863,"text":"because now I have to recreate back to back"},{"time":432424,"text":"what really happened and I had, I'm the only one"},{"time":435479,"text":"who could really blow it at that point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439754,"text":"So this is the footage he photographed,"},{"time":441794,"text":"and it was pretty moving and pretty awe-inspiring."},{"time":446438,"text":"So I'm going to just let it run, so you kind of absorb"},{"time":448935,"text":"this sort of thing, and I'll describe my sort of reactions"},{"time":452136,"text":"when I was looking at it for the very first time."},{"time":454813,"text":"I got the feeling that my brain wanted to basically"},{"time":459379,"text":"see it come back to life."},{"time":460764,"text":"I automatically wanted to see this ship,"},{"time":463485,"text":"this magnificent ship, basically in all its glory,"},{"time":466148,"text":"and conversely, I wanted to see it not in all its glory,"},{"time":469224,"text":"basically go back to what it looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471672,"text":"So I conjured up an effect that I'm later going to show you"},{"time":475132,"text":"what I tried to do, which is kind of the heart of the movie,"},{"time":477537,"text":"for me, and so that's why I wanted to do the movie,"},{"time":481136,"text":"that's why I wanted to create the sort of things I created."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484732,"text":"And I'll show you, you know, another thing that I found"},{"time":486713,"text":"interesting is what we really were emoting to"},{"time":489000,"text":"when you take a look at it."},{"time":490418,"text":"So here's the behind the scenes, a couple of little shots here."},{"time":493324,"text":"So, when you saw my footage,"},{"time":495287,"text":"you were seeing this: basically, a bunch of guys"},{"time":497930,"text":"flipping a ship upside down, and the little Mir subs"},{"time":500927,"text":"are actually about the size of small footballs,"},{"time":503532,"text":"and shot in smoke."},{"time":505565,"text":"Jim went three miles went down, and I went about"},{"time":507775,"text":"three miles away from the studio"},{"time":509373,"text":"and photographed this in a garage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511973,"text":"And so, but what you're emoting to, or what you're looking"},{"time":514204,"text":"at, had the same feeling, the same haunting quality,"},{"time":517316,"text":"that Jim's footage had, so I found it so fascinating"},{"time":520557,"text":"that our brains sort of, once you believe something's real,"},{"time":525049,"text":"you transfer everything that you feel about it,"},{"time":527856,"text":"this quality you have, and it's totally artificial."},{"time":530248,"text":"It's totally make-believe, yet it's not to you,"},{"time":533980,"text":"and I found that that was a very interesting thing"},{"time":535980,"text":"to explore and use, and it caused me to create the next"},{"time":538775,"text":"effect that I'll show you, which is"},{"time":540570,"text":"this sort of magic transition, and all I was really attempting"},{"time":543785,"text":"to do is basically have the audience cue the effect,"},{"time":547738,"text":"so it became a seamless experience for them,"},{"time":550390,"text":"that I wasn't showing you my sort of interpretation,"},{"time":552720,"text":"I was showing you what you wanted to see."},{"time":555641,"text":"And the very next shot, right after this --"},{"time":562424,"text":"So you can see what I was doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563989,"text":"So basically, if there's two subs in the same shot,"},{"time":565783,"text":"I shot it, because where's the camera coming from?"},{"time":568691,"text":"And when Jim shot it, it was only one sub,"},{"time":570252,"text":"because he was photographing from the other,"},{"time":571523,"text":"and I don't remember if I did this or Jim did this."},{"time":573227,"text":"I'll give it to Jim, because he could use the pat on the back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576597,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582915,"text":"Okay. So now the Titanic transition."},{"time":585254,"text":"So this is what I was referring to where I wanted to basically"},{"time":588405,"text":"magically transplant from one state of the Titanic"},{"time":591322,"text":"to the other. So I'll just play the shot once. (Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595270,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598710,"text":"And what I was hoping for is that it just melts in front of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609754,"text":"Gloria Stuart: That was the last time Titanic ever saw daylight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614295,"text":"RL: So, what I did is basically I had another"},{"time":617084,"text":"screening room experience where I was basically tracking"},{"time":619922,"text":"where I was looking, or where we were looking,"},{"time":622224,"text":"and of course you're looking at the two people on the bow"},{"time":624642,"text":"of the ship, and then at some point,"},{"time":626835,"text":"I'm changing the periphery of the shot,"},{"time":628853,"text":"I'm changing, it's becoming the rusted wreck,"},{"time":631175,"text":"and then I would run it every day, and then I would find"},{"time":634184,"text":"exactly the moment that I stopped looking at them"},{"time":637251,"text":"and start noticing the rest of it, and the moment"},{"time":639441,"text":"my eye shifted, we just marked it to the frame."},{"time":641999,"text":"The moment my eye shifted, I immediately started"},{"time":644375,"text":"to change them, so now somehow you missed"},{"time":646714,"text":"where it started and where it stopped."},{"time":649054,"text":"And so I'll just show it one more time."},{"time":651207,"text":"(Music) And it's literally done by using what our brains"},{"time":654404,"text":"naturally do for us, which is, as soon as you shift"},{"time":658139,"text":"your attention, something changes, and then I left"},{"time":660091,"text":"the little scarf going, because it really wanted to be"},{"time":662234,"text":"a ghostly shot, really wanted to feel like they were still"},{"time":666087,"text":"on the wreck, essentially. That's where they were buried forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669417,"text":"Or something like that. I just made that up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671426,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":673895,"text":"It was, incidentally, the last time I ever saw daylight."},{"time":675779,"text":"It was a long film to work on. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":679250,"text":"Now, \"Hugo\" was another interesting movie, because"},{"time":681532,"text":"the movie itself is about film illusions."},{"time":683642,"text":"It's about how our brain is tricked into seeing a persistence"},{"time":686507,"text":"of vision that creates a motion picture,"},{"time":689325,"text":"and one of the things I had to do is, we —"},{"time":692999,"text":"Sasha Baron Cohen is a very clever, very smart guy,"},{"time":696326,"text":"comedian, wanted to basically do an homage to the kind of"},{"time":698477,"text":"the Buster Keaton sort of slapstick things, and he wanted"},{"time":700705,"text":"his leg brace to get caught on a moving train."},{"time":704013,"text":"Very dangerous, very impossible to do, and particularly"},{"time":706134,"text":"on our stage, because there literally is no way to actually"},{"time":709459,"text":"move this train, because it fits so snugly into our set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714323,"text":"So let me show you the scene, and then I basically"},{"time":716786,"text":"used the trick that was identified by Sergei Eisenstein,"},{"time":720469,"text":"which is, if you have a camera that's moving with a moving"},{"time":723643,"text":"object, what is not moving appears to be moving,"},{"time":726412,"text":"and what is moving appears to be stopped,"},{"time":729011,"text":"so what you're actually seeing now is the train is not"},{"time":731926,"text":"moving at all, and what is actually moving is the floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737006,"text":"So this is the shot. That's a little video of"},{"time":740037,"text":"what you're looking at there, which is our little test,"},{"time":743319,"text":"so that's actually what you're seeing, and I thought it was"},{"time":745898,"text":"sort of an interesting thing, because it was, part"},{"time":748055,"text":"of the homage of the movie itself is coming up with this"},{"time":751380,"text":"sort of genius trick which I can't take credit for."},{"time":753898,"text":"I'd love to but I can't, because it was invented"},{"time":756563,"text":"like in 1910 or something like that, is I told Marty,"},{"time":761208,"text":"and it's kind of one of those mind things that it's"},{"time":762864,"text":"really hard to really get until you actually see it work,"},{"time":765245,"text":"and I said, you know, what I was going to do, and he said,"},{"time":768125,"text":"\"So, let me see if I can get this straight. The thing with the wheels?"},{"time":770347,"text":"That doesn't move.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":772300,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":775718,"text":"\"And the thing without the wheels, that moves.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":779694,"text":"Precisely. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782169,"text":"Brings me to the next, and final --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784964,"text":"Marty's not going to see this, is he? (Laughter)"},{"time":789033,"text":"This isn't viewed outside of -- (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792823,"text":"The next illustration is something that, there's like"},{"time":797250,"text":"all one shot theory. It's a very elegant way of telling a story,"},{"time":800312,"text":"especially if you're following somebody on a journey,"},{"time":802369,"text":"and that journey basically tells something about"},{"time":804677,"text":"their personality in a very concise way,"},{"time":806918,"text":"and what we wanted to do based on the shot in \"Goodfellas,\""},{"time":809301,"text":"which is one of the great shots ever,"},{"time":811185,"text":"a Martin Scorsese film, of basically following Henry Hill"},{"time":814562,"text":"through what it feels like to be a gangster walk"},{"time":816698,"text":"going through the Copacabana and being treated in a special way."},{"time":819261,"text":"He was the master of his universe, and we wanted Hugo"},{"time":822768,"text":"to feel the same way, so we created this shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825424,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":828741,"text":"That's Hugo. (Music)"},{"time":833767,"text":"And we felt that if we could basically move the camera"},{"time":836844,"text":"with him, we would feel what it feels like to be this boy"},{"time":839534,"text":"who is basically the master of his universe,"},{"time":842325,"text":"and his universe is, you know, behind the scenes"},{"time":844784,"text":"in the bowels of this particular train station"},{"time":847425,"text":"that only he can actually navigate through"},{"time":849729,"text":"and do it this way, and we had to make it feel that"},{"time":852028,"text":"this is his normal, everyday sort of life,"},{"time":854335,"text":"so the idea of doing it as one shot was very important,"},{"time":856901,"text":"and of course, in shooting in 3D, which is basically"},{"time":859517,"text":"it's a huge camera that's hanging off of a giant stick,"},{"time":863528,"text":"so to recreate a steadycam shot was the task,"},{"time":867050,"text":"and make it feel kind of like what the reaction you got"},{"time":870316,"text":"when you saw the \"Goodfellas\" shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871878,"text":"So what you're now going to see is how we actually did it."},{"time":875679,"text":"It's actually five separate sets shot at five different times"},{"time":878864,"text":"with two different boys."},{"time":880051,"text":"The one on the left is where the shot ends,"},{"time":882213,"text":"and the shot on the right is where it takes over,"},{"time":887639,"text":"and now we switch boys, so it went from Asa Butterfield,"},{"time":891144,"text":"who's the star of the show, to his stand-in. (Music)"},{"time":895018,"text":"I wouldn't say his stunt double. There's a crazy rig"},{"time":896867,"text":"that we built for this. (Music)"},{"time":899331,"text":"And so this is, and now this is set number three"},{"time":902882,"text":"we're into, and then we're going to go into, basically"},{"time":907262,"text":"the very last moment of the shot is actually"},{"time":909926,"text":"the steadycam shot. Everything else was shot on cranes"},{"time":912208,"text":"and various things like that, and it literally was done"},{"time":914253,"text":"over five different sets, two different boys, different times,"},{"time":917550,"text":"and it all had to feel like it was all one shot, and what was"},{"time":920380,"text":"sort of great for me was it was probably"},{"time":925075,"text":"the best-reviewed shot I've ever worked on,"},{"time":927592,"text":"and, you know, I was kind of proud of it when I was done,"},{"time":930180,"text":"which is, you should never really be proud of stuff, I guess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935078,"text":"So I was kind of proud of it, and I went to a friend of mine,"},{"time":937888,"text":"and said, \"You know, this is, you know, kind of"},{"time":939812,"text":"the best-reviewed shot I've ever worked on."},{"time":941684,"text":"What do you think was the reason?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":944595,"text":"And he said, \"Because no one knows"},{"time":946005,"text":"you had anything to do with it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":947971,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":950777,"text":"So, all I can say is, thank you,"},{"time":954691,"text":"and that's my presentation for you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":959891,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}